Urticina spp., Any Urticina species other than U. piscivora and U. lofotensis
anemone, Any anemone including Pachycerianthus fimbriatus

red algae (branching flat blade), Any red alga that has branching, compressed blades that are flat in cross section and roughly 1 cm or greater across. Branching should show a repeating pattern to be distinguished from tearing.

brown algae, Any brown algae but not including Cystoseira, Dicyoneuropsis, Dictyoneurum, Egregia, Macrocystis, Laminariales, Sargassum, Desmarestia (these are distinguished and sampled separately). Typically consists of Colpomenia spp.

red algae (cylindrical branches), Any red alga that has cylindrical to subcylindrical branching thalli. Thalli are not flat in cross section but if so are less than 1 cm across. Examples: Gelidium, Pterocladia, Gastroclonium, Gracilaria, Condracanthus canaliculatus

red alga with cylindrical branches. definition used in 2000, Any red alga that has cylindrical to subcylindrical branching thalli. Thalli are not flat in cross section but if so are less than 1 cm across. Examples: Gelidium, Pterocladia, Gastroclonium, Gracilaria, Condracanthus canaliculatus

tunicate -colonial,compund,social, Includes Clavelina huntsmani, Distaplia occidentalis, Pycnoclavella stanleyi, Metandrocarpa spp. Didemnum carnulentum, Botrylloides spp., Archidistoma molle, Polyclinum planum
coralline algae -crustose, Encrusting or crustose coralline algae
sea cucumber, Any embedded (non-mobile) sea cucumber
cup coral, Includes Balanophyllia elegans, Astrangia lajollaensis, Paracyathus stearnsi
Dictyoneurum, This sp. and Dictyoneuropsis reticulata were considered to be  separate species,  they have since been shown to be all Dictyoneurum californica
Dictyotales, This species group includes Dictyota spp. and Dictyopteris undulata
ornate tube worm, Combined species group of Diopatra ornata and Chaetopterus sp.
red algae -encrusting, Encrusting non-coralline red algae
red fleshy algae, Any upright fleshy red algae recorded by CDFG divers
gorgonian adult, Any gorgonian >3cm tall including Lophogorgia chilensis, Muricea fruticosa and Muricea californica
green algae, Any green algae including Codium, Ulva, Cladophora, Enteromorpha
laminariales recruit, Smaller than adult size laminariales (eg, Macrocystis, Laminaria, Pterygophora, Eisenia, Pleurophycus

red algae (lacy branching), Any red algae that is filamentous or finely, densely branched. Branches are too small to isolate by hand. Examples: Plocamium, Microcladia, Polysiphonia, Ceramium, Neoptilota.
Laminariales holdfast (alive), This species group includes all Laminarian kelp holdfasts except Macrocystis pyrifera

red algae (leaf-like), Any red alga that consists of single or multiple blades that have entire margins and do not branch past the basal portions. Can be torn but will not be in a repeating pattern. Examples: Gigartina, Mazaella, Halymenia, Schizymenia.
sediment/mud, Defined as persistent fine sediment that can't be brushed away by hand
SB 2000 definition of 'Other Red' included all red algae except RHOSPP, BUSHY,  LEAFY, CRUCOR and ERECOR,
SC 2000 definition of 'Other Red' included all red algae except RHOSPP, BUSHY,  LEAFY, CRUCOR and ERECOR,
SC and SB 1999 definition of 'Other Red' included all red algae except RHOSPP, CRUCOR and ERECOR,
diatom layer, Diatom layer or decomposing, flocculent material, Scum""
tube snail, scaled worm shell, Combined species group of Serpulorbis squamigerus and Petaloconchus montereyensis
tunicate -solitary, Includes Corella willmeriana, Ascidia paratropa, Cnemidocarpa finmarkiensis, Styela montereyensis, Boltenia villosa, Halocynthia aurantia, Pyura haustor
tubeworm, Any tube worm (spirorbids, sabellids, serpulids, terrebelids) excluding Dodecacaria, Salmacina, Diopatra and Phragmatopoma (distinguished and sampled separately)
red filamentous turf, Dense turf of red filamentous algae < 1cm high
northern staghorn bryozoan, Added to species list in 2011, previous years lumped into BRYO category
vertical relief: flat, 0 - 10 cm vertical relief recorded within box 0.5 m in front and back of the point and 1 m on either side
vertical relief: high, > 2 m vertical relief recorded within box 0.5 m in front and back of the point and 1 m on either side
vertical relief: moderate, 1 m - 2 m vertical relief recorded within box 0.5 m in front and back of the point and 1 m on either side
vertical relief: slight, 10 cm - 1 m vertical relief recorded within box 0.5 m in front and back of the point and 1 m on either side
substrate: bedrock, Classification based on greatest diameter > 1 m
substrate: boulder, Classification based on greatest diameter 10cm - 1m
substrate: cobble, Classification based on greatest diameter < 10cm
substrate: sand, Classification based on persistent sand that can not be brushed away from any lower substrate
brittlestars (layer above primary spaceholder), A layer of Brittlestars that is counted in addition to a primary space holder below
detritus (layer above primary spaceholder), Unattached algae/kelp detritus that is counted in addition to a primary space holder below
Laminaria farlowii sub-canopy (layer above primary spaceholder), A layer of Laminaria farlowii that is counted in addition to a primary space holder below
Pachythyone rubra (layer above primary spaceholder), A layer of Pachythone rubra that is counted in addition to a primary space holder below
